In [4]:
def get_wheats_dicts(img_dir):

    dataset_dicts = []
    
    images_paths = []
    for dirname, _, filenames in os.walk('/kaggle/input/{}'.format(img_dir)):
        for filename in filenames:
            images_paths.append(os.path.join(dirname, filename))

    print(images_paths)
    
#     dirname, _, filenames in os.walk('/kaggle/input/{}'.format(img_dir))
#     images_paths = [os.path.join(dirname, file) for file in filenames]
        
    for i, path in enumerate(images_paths):
        record = {}

        height, width = cv2.imread(path).shape[:2]

        record["file_name"] = path
        record["image_id"] = i
        record["height"] = height
        record["width"] = width

        dataset_dicts.append(record)

    return dataset_dicts

In [7]:
def show_all(image_list, title_list, num_images=3, inarow=1):
    plt.figure(figsize=[100,100])
    assert len(image_list) == len(title_list), "Houston we've got a problem"
    N = len(image_list)
    lines = int(N / inarow)+1
    for index, (img, title) in enumerate(zip(image_list, title_list)):
        if index >= num_images:
            break
        plt.subplot(lines, inarow, index+1)
        plt.imshow(img.get_image())
        plt.title(title)

In [10]:
def format_prediction_string(boxes, scores):
    pred_strings = []
    for j in zip(scores, boxes):
        pred_strings.append("{0:.4f} {1} {2} {3} {4}".format(j[0], j[1][0], j[1][1], j[1][2], j[1][3]))
    return " ".join(pred_strings)

    cfg.MODEL.RETINANET.SCORE_THRESH_TEST = 0.5
else:
    cfg.MODEL.ROI_HEADS.SCORE_THRESH_TEST = 0.5
    cfg.MODEL.ROI_HEADS.NUM_CLASSES = 1

cfg.DATASETS.TEST = ("wheat_test", )
predictor = DefaultPredictor(cfg)

# dataset_dicts_pred = get_wheats_dicts('global-wheat-detection/', "jpg", mode='test')
output_list = []
predictions = []
out_images = []

for d in dataset_dicts:
    im = cv2.imread(d["file_name"])
    outputs = predictor(im)

    im_id = d['file_name'].split('/')[-1][:-4]
    boxes = outputs['instances'].get_fields()['pred_boxes'].to("cpu").tensor.numpy().astype(int)
    scores = outputs['instances'].get_fields()['scores'].to("cpu").numpy()

    boxes[:, 2] = boxes[:, 2] - boxes[:, 0]
    boxes[:, 3] = boxes[:, 3] - boxes[:, 1]
    
    result = {
            'image_id': im_id,
            'PredictionString': format_prediction_string(boxes, scores)
        }
    predictions.append(result)

    v = Visualizer(im[:, :, ::-1],
                  metadata=wheats_metadata, 
                  scale=0.5
    )
    out = v.draw_instance_predictions(outputs["instances"].to("cpu"))
    
    out_images.append(out)
    output_list.append(outputs)
